s CA$3.95/month. </p>\n<h3>10. Web Hosting Canada</h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/web-hosting-canada.jpg\" alt=\"web-hosting-canada\" width=\"740\" height=\"369\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-235108\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/web-hosting-canada.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/web-hosting-canada-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Web Hosting Canada is based in Montreal, Quebec and is trusted by over 30,000 small businesses. This Canadian web hosting provider is one of the few that offers servers on both the East and West coasts. So, no matter where in Canada your users are located, you can count on them to deliver fast speeds.  </p>\n<p>Aside from web hosting services, Web Hosting Canada also offers domain names, a Weebly website builder, email and online marketing services, security and SSL certificates, and more. </p>\n<p>They also provide 24/7 bilingual, expert support via telephone, chat, and email. </p>\n<p><strong>Servers in Canada</strong>: Yes, Toronto and Vancouver, Canada. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Regular pricing starts at CA$5.99/month. </p>\n<p><strong>Special Offer</strong>: You can get started for only CA$3.89/month. </p>\n<h3>How to Choose the Best Canadian Hosting</h3>\n<p>There are a number of factors you should consider when choosing Canadian hosting, including: </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Server Location</li>\n<li>Uptime</li>\n<li>Features</li>\n<li>Customer Support</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Let’s look at each of these factors more closely so that you can easily choose the best Canadian hosting for your needs. </p>\n<p><strong>1. Server Location</strong><br />\nThe speed of your website is important. Slow web page loading times can negatively affect your SEO, the user experience, and even conversions. So, if you want to provide a speedy website to users, you need to look at server location. That’s why we’ve included server locations of each web hosting provider in this article.<br />\nThe location of a server actually affects the loading time of your website. The closer a website or a user is to a data center, the faster they’ll be able to access your website. </p>\n<p>If you’re making a Canadian website and expect most of your users to be located in Canada, you may want to choose a web hosting provider that has servers located in Canada. But, as long as the server is close by (for instance, in the United States) and it’s a decent server, you should still be able to get lightning fast speed.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Uptime</strong><br />\nIt’s important that your website is available to users at all times. If your website is down often, you can lose out on a lot of traffic, leads, and sales. So, it’s important to look for Canadian web hosting that offers a great uptime guarantee. </p>\n<p>Uptime is simply the measure of time that a server is working and available. It’s pretty impossible to guarantee a 100% uptime, but anything below 99.9% is fairly unreliable. </p>\n<p><strong>3. Features</strong><br />\nCreating a website shouldn’t be hard. Especially as a beginner, you’ll want to choose a web hosting service that offers everything you need to get started. </p>\n<p>Features to look out for include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Domain Name</li>\n<li>SSL Certificate</li>\n<li>1-Click WordPress Installation </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-website-builders-for-beginners-compared/\">Website Builder</a></li>\n<li>Email Accounts</li>\n<li>Storage Space</li>\n<li>Backups</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>4. Customer Support</strong><br />\nIf something goes wrong with your site, it’s important to know that you can get friendly, knowledgeable, and fast support. Look for web hosting that offers 24/7 support so that you don’t have to wait hours or days for a response. </p>\n<h3>Our Verdict: What is the Best Canadian Web Hosting?</h3>\n<p>We recommend Bluehost as our #1 pick for the best Canadian hosti