\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/query-string-of-repeatw3tc-on-url/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1430:\"<p>Replies: 4</p>\n						<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m having pages from my staging multi-site re-directed to ones with query string of <code>repeat=w3tc</code>. Although it&#8217;s 307 Redirection, it&#8217;s constantly redirecting.</p>\n<p>After some dig up on the code and discussion from <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/how-to-remove-repeatw3tc-from-url-in-multisite/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://wordpress.org/support/topic/how-to-remove-repeatw3tc-from-url-in-multisite/</a>, I soon found out it was due to the port that I used on my staging multi-site. For example, if my site&#8217;s URL is <code>www.staging-site.com:8080/site-2</code>, file <code>wp-content/cache/blogs.php</code> would save this site as <code>www.staging-site.com8080/site-2</code>, which I believe is due to this line of code <code>$blog_home_url = preg_replace( \'/[^a-zA-Z0-9\\+\\.%~!()\\/\\-\\_]/\', \'\', $blog_home_url );</code> in file <code>Util_WpmuBlogmap.php</code>.</p>\n<p>My production multi-site has no such issue since it doesn&#8217;t have any port number, but I still think this issue should be addressed; either we change the regex to include colon <code>:</code>, or we use the processed string of <code>$blog_home_url</code> to check if <code>$blog_ids</code> contains this entry.</p>\n<p>Regards.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/MqjeFZMKWRU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/eleme