terinsights.com/best-wordpress-lms-plugins/\">7 Best WordPress LMS Plugins: Which Is Best for You?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17058:\"<p>Are you looking to create an online course in WordPress? Want to know which is the best WordPress LMS plugin? </p>\n<p>An LMS (Learning Management System) plugin is a piece of WordPress software with an ability to create and run an online course in WordPress. LMS plugins help you to build a website like Udemy, Treehouse, DigitalMarketer, etc. and earn money by selling online courses. </p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll compare the 7 best WordPress LMS plugins 2019 to help you choose the best one for your needs. </p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/learndash/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. LearnDash</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/learndash/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/learndashlmspluginwordpress.png\" alt=\"LearnDash Best WordPress LMS Management Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-194246\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/learndashlmspluginwordpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/learndashlmspluginwordpress-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/learndash/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">LearnDash</a> is the most popular LMS plugin for WordPress. Trusted by Fortune 500 companies, top universities, and training centers, it offers simply the best way to create and sell online courses with WordPress. </p>\n<p>Here’re the top features of LearnDash plugin. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Powerful drag and drop course builder for creating multi-layer courses.</li>\n<li>Drip-feed (schedule) content options – “X Days” after enrollment or specific date.</li>\n<li>Create advanced quizzes using 8 different question types.</li>\n<li>Award learners with points, certificates, and badges and encourage learning.</li>\n<li>Set one-time price, subscriptions, or membership access to your courses.</li>\n<li>Accept payments with popular payment gateways including PayPal, Stripe, and 2Checkout.</li>\n<li>Front-end user profiles for students to track their course activity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>LearnDash is a leader in the e-learning industry. Their team offers expert support via support tickets. They also have extensive documentation with easy to use guides and tutorials. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starting from $159 / year for 1 site license. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/learndash/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Get started with LearnDash today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/lifterlms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. LifterLMS</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/lifterlms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lifterlms.png\" alt=\"LifterLMS Powerful LMS Plugin for WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"310\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213732\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lifterlms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lifterlms-300x150.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/lifterlms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">LifterLMS</a> is a powerful online course builder software for WordPress sites. It comes with a full set of tools to let you create, sell, and protect engaging online courses in WordPress. </p>\n<p>Here’re the top features of LifterLMS plugin. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Supports multimedia including video, audio, text, and images for lessons. </li>\n<li>User-friendly multi-tier drag and drop course builder for creating lessons fast.</li>\n<li>Content dripping and course prerequisites to deliver content over time.</li>\n<li>Create multimedia quizzes, set quiz timer, and engage students.</li>\n<li>Multi instructor support, and discussion areas.</li>\n<li>One-time payment or recurring payments, sell course bundles, coupons, etc.</li>\n<li>Offer achievement badges, certificates, and boost engagement.</li>\n<li>Integrates well with <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/\">WordPress form plugins</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-email-newsletter-tools-compared-pros-and-cons/\">email marketing tools</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>LifterLMS offers dedicated customer support via live chat, support tickets, and detailed documentation on their website. </p>\n<p>An advantage of using LifterLMS is that you can easily track your LifterLMS eCommerce data with MonsterInsights Google Analytics plugin. MonsterInsights seamlessly <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-monsterinsights-7-7-lifterlms-integration/\">integrates with LifterLMS</a> and lets you set up tracking with just one click. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Individual addons for $99 each / year or Universe Bundle for $299 / year (Free version is also available).  </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/lifterlms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Get started with LifterLMS today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/teachable/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Teachable</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/teachable/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/teachable.png\" alt=\"Teachable Powerful Online Course Builder Platform\" width=\"620\" height=\"386\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213733\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/teachable.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/teachable-300x187.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/teachable/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Teachable</a> is yet another powerful online course builder plugin available on the market. Unlike LearnDash and LifterLMS, it’s a standalone SaaS (Software as a Service) platform for online course creation. </p>\n<p>However, you can easily add your Teachable online courses to your WordPress site by using a subdomain. Or you can simply start with a Teachable subdomain like www.yourschool.teachable.com. </p>\n<p>Here’re the top features of Teachable.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Allows you to create engaging multimedia lectures using video, image, audio, and PDF files.</li>\n<li>Powerful course editor for creating beautiful course pages.</li>\n<li>Lets you create quizzes, discussion forums, and issue course completion certificates.</li>\n<li>Use coupons and promotions to boost your sales.</li>\n<li>Create your own affiliate program and reward others for helping you grow your sales.</li>\n<li>Accept payments from 130+ international currencies through PayPal or Stripe.</li>\n<li>Seamless integration with marketing tools like <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/mailchimp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">MailChimp</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/aweber/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">AWeber</a>, etc.</li>\n<li>Built-in reporting tools to view total sales, revenue, and students’ progress.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Teachable is a fully hosted platform, so you don’t need to worry about backups and updates. The Teachable team offers 24/7 monitoring to keep your online courses up and running. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starting from $29 / month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/teachable/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Get started with Teachable today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://flyplugins.com/wp-courseware/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. WP Courseware</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://flyplugins.com/wp-courseware/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpcourseware.png\" alt=\"WP Courseware Best WordPress Online Course Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"374\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213734\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpcourseware.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpcourseware-300x181.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://flyplugins.com/wp-courseware/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WP Courseware</a> is yet another popular online course creation tool for WordPress. It offers a hassle-free way to create online courses with the drag and drop course builder. </p>\n<p>Here’re the top features of WP Courseware. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Drip (schedule) content to be realeased by date or at specific intervals.</li>\n<li>Create powerful quizzes using timers, retake limits, reporting, and surveys.</li>\n<li>Quiz grade books to view quiz results, progress reports of students.</li>\n<li>Provide downloadable and customizable course certificates.</li>\n<li>Easy to integrate with eCommerce and membership plugins.</li>\n<li>Built-in shopping cart with options to connect Stripe or PayPal.</li>\n<li>Works well with most WordPress themes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>WP Courseware offers support via Member Portal, which is a support hub for their logged in users. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starting from $129 / year for 2-site license.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://flyplugins.com/wp-courseware/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Get started with WP Courseware today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://thimpress.com/product/wordpress-lms-plugin-learnpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. LearnPress</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://thimpress.com/product/wordpress-lms-plugin-learnpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/learnpress.png\" alt=\"LearnPress Free WordPress LMS Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"230\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213735\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/learnpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/learnpress-300x111.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://thimpress.com/product/wordpress-lms-plugin-learnpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">LearnPress</a> is a free WordPress LMS plugin available on WordPress.org plugin repository. You can download and use it on as many sites as you like completely for free. However, you’ll need to buy their premium addons for advanced features. </p>\n<p>Here’re the top features of LearnPress plugin.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create unlimited courses, lessons, quizzes, and questions with ease.</li>\n<li>Add text, images, PowerPoint slideshow, documents, and anything to your lessons.</li>\n<li>Set requirements for students to take a lesson with premium addons like Content Drip and Prerequisite.</li>\n<li>Monitor learners’ progress, scores, and results with Gradebook addon.</li>\n<li>Use LearnPress WooCommerce for eCommerce features, and payment settings.</li>\n<li>Supports Stripe, 2Checkout, Authorize.Net, and more for accepting payments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>LearnPress users can get support via forum. Free users can use WordPress.org support forum while paid users have access to a more dedicated support forum on their site. You can also use their documentation page for frequently asked general support queries. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free. (Paid addons available for advanced features)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://thimpress.com/product/wordpress-lms-plugin-learnpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Get started with LearnPress today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/sensei/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. WooCommerce Sensei</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/sensei/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/woocommercesensei.png\" alt=\"WooCommerce Sensei WordPress LMS Plugin Free\" width=\"620\" height=\"290\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213736\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/woocommercesensei.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/woocommercesensei-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/sensei/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WooCommerce Sensei</a> is powerful WordPress LMS plugin built by the team behind WooCommerce. It’s a free LMS plugin which enables you to launch your online course without hiring a WordPress developer. </p>\n<p>Here’re the top Sensei features.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Beginner-friendly LMS platform for building a WordPress training site.</li>\n<li>Seamless WooCommerce integration and powerful addons to add features.</li>\n<li>Create engaging quizzes that help to strengthen the learners’ understanding.</li>\n<li>Many free and paid addons available to expand the features of the plugin.</li>\n<li>BuddyPress for Sensei addon helps you turn your course website into social education platform.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>WooCommerce for Sensei users find answers of commonly asked questions in their FAQ page. For technical support, you can log into the plugin forum on WordPress.org or contact WooCommerce team.</p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free. (Paid addons available for advanced features)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/sensei/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Get started with WooCommerce Sensei today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/tutor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">7. Tutor LMS</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/tutor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/tutorlms.png\" alt=\"Tutor LMS Free WordPress Learning Management System LMS Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213737\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/tutorlms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/tutorlms-300x97.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/tutor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tutor LMS</a> is a free WordPress LMS plugin you can use to create, manage, and sell online courses. Like most LMS plugins, it comes with a user-friendly course builder which lets you create a full-fledged online school and offer education to the students. </p>\n<p>Here’re the top Tutor LMS features.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create unlimited courses and lessons easily.</li>\n<li>Add video lessons self-hosted on your server, or embed from YouTube and Vimeo.</li>\n<li>Frontend student dashboard </li>\n<li>Create advanced quizzes with quiz timer, and quiz attempts.</li>\n<li>Course review and rating system.</li>\n<li>Show course difficulty level, course duration, and also trailer / teaser.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For support, you can post your questions in the support forum on WordPress.org or their website. Also, you can see their simple tutorials on the documentation. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/tutor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Get started with Tutor LMS plugin today!</a></p>\n<h3>Which is the Best WordPress LMS Plugin</h3>\n<p>After reviewing the most popular LMS plugins available, we conclude that <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/learndash/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">LearnDash</a> is the best choice for creating and selling online courses. With its advanced features and powerful integrations, it’s the WINNER of LMS plugin comparison. </p>\n<p>A close competitor, as well as a perfect LearnDash alternative, is the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/lifterlms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">LifterLMS</a> plugin. Similar to LearnDash, it includes advanced features which let you build a great learning center with WordPress. </p>\n<p>An exclusive advantage of using LifterLMS is that you can track your plugin eCommerce data easily using <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/ecommerce/\">MonsterInsights eCommerce addon</a>. </p>\n<p>If you want to use a standalone LMS software, then <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/teachable/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Teachable</a> is the right tool for you. LearnPress, WooCommerce Sensei and Tutor LMS are great plugins for users looking for a free LMS tool. </p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to find the best LMS plugins for WordPress. You may also want to see our handpicked list of <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-popup-plugins/\">best WordPress popup plugins</a>. </p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more useful WordPress showcases and Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-lms-plugins/\">7 Best WordPress LMS Plugins: Which Is Best for You?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-lms-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"How to Track Form Abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:161:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 01 Jul 2019 18:34:17 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"forms tracking\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"forms addon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"tracking form abandonment\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"wordpress forms tracking\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=213080\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:608:\"<p>Do you want to track form abandonment on your WordPress site? As forms are major points of interaction on a website, tracking form abandonment on your site lets you know how well users are engaged with your forms and other content. In this article, we’ll show you how to easily track form abandonment in WordPress [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress/\">How to Track Form Abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12408:\"<p>Do you want to track form abandonment on your WordPress site? </p>\n<p>As forms are major points of interaction on a website, tracking form abandonment on your site lets you know how well users are engaged with your forms and other content. </p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to easily track form abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way). </p>\n<h3>Tracking Form Abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-complete-beginners-guide-to-google-analytics-for-wordpress/\">Google Analytics</a> is the most widely used web analytics tool for tracking website traffic, conversions, and more. </p>\n<p>It lets you track a wide variety of metrics including <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-ecommerce-sales-in-google-analytics/\">eCommerce transactions</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-your-wordpress-form-conversions-in-google-analytics/\">form conversions</a>, form abandonment, and more, however using it is a bit tricky. </p>\n<p>If you’re a beginner, then you’ll need to invest lots of your time to understand <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-does-google-analytics-work-beginners-guide/\">how Google Analytics works</a>. Not only that you also need to spend money to hire a developer for configuring advanced metrics. </p>\n<p>But thankfully, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> plugin makes it super easy for WordPress users. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/monsterinsightsbestgapluginforwordpress.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Best Google Analytics Plugin for WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"320\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-186638\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/monsterinsightsbestgapluginforwordpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/monsterinsightsbestgapluginforwordpress-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It lets you configure form abandonment tracking and other important metrics in WordPress with just a few steps. </p>\n<p>To get started, you need to install and activate the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights plugin</a> and then connect it with your Google Analytics account. For detailed instructions, see our step by step guide on how to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">install Google Analytics in WordPress with MonsterInsights</a>. </p>\n<p>After that, you need to install the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/forms/\">MonsterInsights Forms addon</a> for tracking your forms. Go to <strong>MonsterInsights &raquo; Addons</strong> page from your dashboard and then install the Forms addon. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installmiformsaddon.png\" alt=\"Install MonsterInsights Forms Addon\" width=\"620\" height=\"168\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213104\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installmiformsaddon.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installmiformsaddon-300x81.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s all! Now MonsterInsights will automatically start tracking your WordPress forms. </p>\n<p>If you want to reconfirm that, then you need to visit the <strong>MonsterInsights &raquo; Settings</strong> page and click on the Conversions tab. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/miformstrackingsettings.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Forms Tracking Settings\" width=\"620\" height=\"406\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213105\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/miformstrackingsettings.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/miformstrackingsettings-300x196.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As shown in the screenshot above, the plugin will automatically detect your form plugin, and enable forms tracking. It supports all the major <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/\">WordPress form plugins</a> like <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a>, <a href=\"https://formidableforms.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Formidable Forms</a>, and more. </p>\n<p>After that, you may need to wait sometime to view your reports. It can take a few hours to 48 hours for Google Analytics to collect fresh data. </p>\n<h3>Viewing Your WordPress Form Tracking Stats</h3>\n<p>You can view your WordPress form tracking reports by going to <strong>MonsterInsights &raquo; Reports &raquo; Forms</strong> from your dashboard. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsightsformsreport.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Forms Tracking Reports\" width=\"620\" height=\"406\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213106\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsightsformsreport.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsightsformsreport-300x196.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The MonsterInsights Forms report shows the total number of impressions, conversions, and conversion rate for each WordPress form. </p>\n<p>Now you can easily find out the number of people who abandoned your form. Wouldn’t it be great if more people who viewed your form fill it out?</p>\n<p>You can view this report also in your Google Analytics account. Simply click on the ‘View Full Forms Report’ button in your MonsterInsights forms report, and it will redirect you to the top events page in Google Analytics. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gatopevents-wpformsreports.png\" alt=\"Google Analytics Top Events Report - Forms Conversions\" width=\"620\" height=\"327\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213107\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gatopevents-wpformsreports.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gatopevents-wpformsreports-300x158.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As Google Analytics treats forms related actions as events, forms tracking reports are shown under the Events category. </p>\n<p>By default, you can see the stats for event action. You can click on the ‘Event Label’ link to see the performance of your individual forms. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eventlabelgatopevents.png\" alt=\"View Event Label for Google Analytics Events\" width=\"620\" height=\"275\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213108\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eventlabelgatopevents.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eventlabelgatopevents-300x133.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>Recovering the Leads from the Abandoned Forms Using WPForms</h3>\n<p>Form abandonment is the real problem that you will miss your potential leads/ customers at the last point. But <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a> users can now solve that problem and turn those abandoning users into loyal customers. </p>\n<p>WPForms is the most user-friendly as well as the most powerful WordPress form plugin in the market. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms-wordpress-form-builder-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"WPForms Best WordPress Form Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-158461\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms-wordpress-form-builder-plugin.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms-wordpress-form-builder-plugin-300x121.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It allows you to easily <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form-in-wordpress-the-simple-way/\">create simple contact forms</a> to advanced forms like <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-survey-in-wordpress/\">surveys</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-an-order-form-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/\">order forms</a>, multi-page forms, and more in your WordPress blog. </p>\n<p>WPForms comes with an exclusive <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-abandonment-addon/\" target=\"_blank\">Form Abandonment addon</a> to help you recover leads from the abandoned forms. The addon saves partial entries and lets you follow up with the interested prospects. </p>\n<p>This feature is especially useful for support request forms, order forms, request quote forms, etc. For any reason, the users may have abandoned your form, but you can follow up and build new relationships with them. </p>\n<p>To use the addon, go to <strong>WPForms &raquo; Addons</strong> page and then install the Form Abandonment Addon. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installformabandonmentaddonwpforms.png\" alt=\"Install Form Abandonment Addon WPForms Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"191\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213109\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installformabandonmentaddonwpforms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installformabandonmentaddonwpforms-300x92.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, you need to enable this option in your WordPress forms. If you’ve existing forms, then you need to edit them and enable this option. </p>\n<p>For example, we’ll edit Billing / Order Form in our demo website. </p>\n<p>In your form editor screen, click on the ‘Settings’ menu. After that, click the ‘Form Abandonment’ option and check the box next to ‘Enable form abandonment lead capture.’ </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms.png\" alt=\"Enable Form Abandonment Lead Capture in WPForms\" width=\"620\" height=\"278\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213110\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s all! Now WPForms will record the entries for the abandoned forms and lets you optimize them. </p>\n<p>Like all the other entries, you can find the abandoned form entries as well in the Entries menu. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms.png\" alt=\"Entry Status of Abandoned and Completed Forms\" width=\"518\" height=\"410\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213111\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms.png 518w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms-300x237.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 518px) 100vw, 518px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you can contact these users and offer them the products they may be interested in. </p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to learn how to track form abandonment in WordPress – the easy way. And also to learn to how to recover leads from the abandoned forms using WPForms. </p>\n<p>You may also want to see our step by step guide on how to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-google-analytics-to-amp-pages-on-wordpress/\">track your AMP traffic using Google Analytics</a>. </p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress/\">How to Track Form Abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"35+ Best WordPress Plugins 2019 (Grow Your Website FASTER!)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:169:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-marketers/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=best-wordpress-plugins-and-t